<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />

  <title>Privacy Policy - Taskify</title>

  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/styles/main.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/styles/partials/nav.css" />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/static/styles/partials/footer.css" />

  <style>
    .privacy-container {
      max-width: 800px;
      margin: 120px auto 50px;
      padding: 0 24px;
      line-height: 1.6;
    }

    .privacy-container h1 {
      font-size: 32px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }

    .privacy-container h2 {
      font-size: 24px;
      margin-top: 30px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .privacy-container ul {
      margin: 12px 0 20px 24px;
    }

    .privacy-container li {
      margin-bottom: 10px;
    }

  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <%- include("partials/nav.ejs") %>

  <main class="privacy-container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p>Last updated: May 2026</p>

    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>
      Welcome to Taskify. This Privacy Policy explains what information the project uses,
      how cookie and local storage preferences are handled, and what choices users have.
    </p>

    <h2>2. Data We Collect</h2>
    <p>
      Taskify is a coursework project. The current website mainly uses browser storage to remember
      basic user preferences, such as cookie choices and site preferences. We do not sell personal data.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Cookies and Local Storage</h2>
    <p>
      We use cookies or local storage to support essential website behaviour and remember user choices.
      For example, when a user accepts or rejects optional cookies, that choice is stored locally in the
      browser so the banner does not appear repeatedly.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Cookie Categories</h2>
    <p>
      Taskify separates cookie preferences into the following categories:
    </p>

    <ul>
      <li>
        <strong>Essential cookies:</strong> Required for basic website operation and cookie consent storage.
        These are always active.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Preference storage:</strong> Used to remember optional interface preferences, such as language
        or display choices.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Analytics preferences:</strong> Used to store whether the user agrees to anonymous usage
        analytics. This project does not load third-party analytics by default.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Your Choices</h2>
    <p>
      Users can accept all cookies, reject optional cookies, or customize their preferences through the
      cookie banner. Users can also clear cookies and local storage at any time through their browser settings.
    </p>

    <h2>6. Contact</h2>
    <p>
      If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy, please contact the Taskify project team.
    </p>
  </main>

  <%- include("partials/footer.ejs") %>
</body>

</html>